This paper presents a comparative study of four deep learning frameworks and evaluates their performance on several types of deep learning architectures. The study focuses on aspects such as extensibility, hardware utilization, and speed, which are all related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
